{
  "stem": "16930.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "In the case of my sister's, people she went to, they assumed ownership.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They-- they sort of thought they had adopted her, that they belonged to them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was part of them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A lot of people who were-- who were looking for adoptions-- and you know this as a social worker-- are not qualified to be adoptive parents because they want to have the kid for their own benefit, to fill a void in their-- in their-- a void in their lives which they feel a child might-- might fill.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sometimes it does and sometimes it doesn't.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they sort of have an idea this kid belongs to me and, you know, it's part of me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I, you know-- has to-- but the people I was with did not have this attitude.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when they saw that I balked at going to church-- and they understood-- they-- they agreed-- they sort arranged for me to leave.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So-- and we parted on good terms.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I maintained a relationship with them by-- by letters, occasional visits, until their deaths-- until-- until their death.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "About four months.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "About four months.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe five months.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't exactly, you know?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When you're a kid, you don't keep records, you know?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Maybe four-- about maybe four or five months-- and not that long, but long enough to establish relationships with them and their extended family, which lived around in the village, at different farms in the village.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The-- my the-- the people I was with, the man, he was a farm worker-- didn't have his own farm.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the wife was just a housewife.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She took care of things in the house and of-- my-- took care of me and took care of her husband.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
